// zaimki osobowe w funkcji podmiotu
Ćwiczenie 1. Wstaw odpowiedni zaimek.
mother --> she
father --> he
mouse --> it
balls --> they
Lucy --> she
boys --> they
school --> it
bike --> it
Adam and I --> we
Adam and Lucy --> they

// to be
Ćwiczenie 1. Wstaw czasownik to be w odpowiedniej formie.
You are actors.
She is a teacher.
He is a student.
I am a doctor.
We are policemen.
They are waiters.
You are a journalist.
It is a dog.

Ćwiczenie 2. Utwórz przeczenia z czasownikiem to be.
They are not at school. lub They aren't at school.
He is not my father. lub He isn't my father.
You are not tall. lub You aren't tall..
I am not a man.
It is not a dog. lub It isn't a dog.
We are not studying. lub We aren't studying..
She is not a doctor. lub She isn't a doctor.
You are not French. lub You aren't French..

Ćwiczenie 3. Utwórz pytania z czasownikiem to be.
Czy oni są zmęczeni? --> Are they tired?
Czy to jest chomik? --> Is it a hamster?
Czy jesteś w domu? --> Are you at home?
Czy wieloryby są bardzo duże? --> Are whales very big?
Czy ona jest tenisistką? --> Is she a tennis player?
Czy on jest twoim chłopakiem? --> Is he your boyfriend?
Czy ja jestem chory? (pytając siebie) --> Am I sick?

Ćwiczenie 4. Odpowiedz na pytania używając krótkich odpowiedzi.
Are you from England? 1) Yes, I am. 2) No, I am not.
Are you 12? 1) Yes, I am. 2) No, I am not.
Is she nice? 1) Yes, she is. 2) No, she isn't. lub 2) No, she's not.
Are your parents from Poland? 1) Yes, they are. 2) No, they aren’t. lub 2) No, they’re not
Are we students? 1) Yes, we are. 2) No, we aren’t. lub 2) No, we’re not.
Am I your friend? 1) Yes, you are. 2) No, you aren't. lub 2) No, you're not.
Is your school bag black? 1) Yes, it is. 2) No, it isn't. lub 2) No, it's not.
Are the friends at school? 1) Yes, they are. 2) No, they aren’t. lub 2) No, they’re not
Is the dog in the garden? 1) Yes, it is. 2) No, it isn't. lub 2) No, it's not.
Is he a teacher? 1) Yes, he is. 2) No, he isn't. lub 2) No, he's not.

// Liczba mnoga
Ćwiczenie 1. Stwórz liczbę mnogą podanych niżej rzeczowników.
banana --> bananas
key --> keys
church --> churches
knife --> knives
egg --> eggs
toy --> toys
donkey --> donkeys
tree --> trees
radio --> radios
wolf --> wolves
horse --> horses
kangaroo --> kangaroos
cow --> cows
day --> days
box --> boxes
leaf --> leaves
window --> windows
child --> children
family --> families
mouse --> mice

Ćwiczenie 2. Wpisz w odpowiednie ramki liczbę mnogą podanych niżej rzeczowników.
branch, sheep, library, wife, chair, house, cherry, octopus, wolf, pear, lorry, piano,
foot, fish, goose, city, photo, hero, apple, giraffe, parrot, dress, ferry, leaf.
-s: chairs, houses, pears, pianos, photos, apples, giraffes, parrots
-es: branches, octopuses, heroes, dresses
-ies: libraries, cherries, lorries, cities, ferries
-ves: wives, wolves, leaves
rzeczowniki nieregularne: sheep, feet, fish, geese

// rzeczowniki policzalne i niepoliczalne
a bar of chocolate.
a cup of coffee.
a glass of orange juice. / a carton of orange juice.
a can of Coke.
a glass of wine. / a bottle of wine.
a bar of soap.
a slice of bread. / a loaf of bread.
a cap of tea.
a glass of lemonade. / a bottle of lemonade.
a tin of beans.

furniture, table, chair, desk --> furniture
potato, carrot, cucumber, soup --> soup
coffee, cup, glass, bottle --> coffee
sheep, meat, dog, cat --> meat
apple, orange, chocolate, banana --> chocolate
glass, bottle, coke, water --> water
loaf, slice, bread, cake --> bread
tree, flower, wood, leaf --> wood
